The paper deals with a computer vision problem of segmenting echogram radar data, which is a typical problem in the computer vision subfield of image segmentation (cs.CV). The paper proposes a deep learning model that combines 3D ConvNets and RNNs, which is a typical approach in the machine learning subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions that the proposed model avoids the need for hand-tuned parameters, which is a typical feature of the artificial intelligence subfield of automated machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also mentions that the proposed model is faster, which is a typical feature of the robotics subfield of real-time systems (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with a structured prediction problem, which is a typical problem in the neural networks subfield of sequence modeling (cs.NE).
